#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.44"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.44:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.44:0.2"
msgid "5. Muṇḍarājavagga"
msgstr "5. With King Muṇḍa"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.44:0.3"
msgid "44. Manāpadāyīsutta"
msgstr "44. Agreeable"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "an5.44:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena uggassa "
"gahapatino vesālikassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of the householder Ugga of Vesālī, where he sat on the seat "
"spread out."

msgctxt "an5.44:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggo gahapati vesāliko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggo "
"gahapati vesāliko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Ugga went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to "
"him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:2.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an5.44:2.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr "‘The giver of the agreeable gets the agreeable.’"

#. VAR: sālapupphakaṃ → sālipupphakaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.44:2.3"
msgid "Manāpaṃ me, bhante, sālapupphakaṃ khādanīyaṃ;"
msgstr "My sal flower porridge is agreeable:"

msgctxt "an5.44:2.4"
msgid "taṃ me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "may the Buddha please accept it from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:2.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted it out of compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:3.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an5.44:3.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr "‘The giver of the agreeable gets the agreeable.’"

#. VAR: sampannakolakaṃ sūkaramaṃsaṃ → sampannasūkaramaṃsaṃ (bj) | sampannavarasūkaramaṃsaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.44:3.3"
msgid "Manāpaṃ me, bhante, sampannakolakaṃ sūkaramaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr "My pork with jujube is agreeable:"

msgctxt "an5.44:3.4"
msgid "taṃ me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "may the Buddha please accept it from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:3.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted it out of compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:4.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.44:4.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: nibbattatelakaṃ → nibaddhatelakaṃ (bj-a) | nibbaṭṭatelakaṃ (s-a) | nibbaddhatelakaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.44:4.3"
msgid "Manāpaṃ me, bhante, nibbattatelakaṃ nāliyasākaṃ;"
msgstr "“… My fried vegetable stalks are agreeable:"

msgctxt "an5.44:4.4"
msgid "taṃ me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "may the Buddha please accept them from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:4.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted them out of compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:5.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.44:5.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: vicitakāḷako → vigatakāḷako (s1-3, km, pts1) | vigatakālako (mr)
msgctxt "an5.44:5.3"
msgid "Manāpo me, bhante, sālīnaṃ odano vicitakāḷako anekasūpo anekabyañjano;"
msgstr ""
"“… My boiled fine rice with the dark grains picked out, served with many "
"soups and sauces is agreeable:"

msgctxt "an5.44:5.4"
msgid "taṃ me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "may the Buddha please accept it from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:5.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted it out of compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.50"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:6.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.44:6.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.44:6.3"
msgid "Manāpāni me, bhante, kāsikāni vatthāni;"
msgstr "“… My cloths imported from Kāsī are agreeable:"

msgctxt "an5.44:6.4"
msgid "tāni me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "may the Buddha please accept them from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:6.5"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted them out of compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:7.1"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.44:7.2"
msgid "‘manāpadāyī labhate manāpan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo → kādalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo (bj)
msgctxt "an5.44:7.3"
msgid ""
"Manāpo me, bhante, pallaṅko gonakatthato paṭalikatthato "
"kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo sauttaracchado ubhatolohitakūpadhāno."
msgstr ""
"“… My couch spread with woolen covers—shag-piled or embroidered with flowers—"
"and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy above and red pillows at "
"both ends is agreeable."

msgctxt "an5.44:7.4"
msgid "Api ca, bhante, mayampetaṃ jānāma:"
msgstr "But, sir, I know that"

msgctxt "an5.44:7.5"
msgid "‘netaṃ bhagavato kappatī’ti."
msgstr "this is not proper for the Buddha."

# Accepting BB’s variant reading of 1000. There is a general underlying tendency to exaggerate numbers, so choosing the lower is usually better.
msgctxt "an5.44:7.6"
msgid "Idaṃ me, bhante, candanaphalakaṃ agghati adhikasatasahassaṃ;"
msgstr "However, this plank of sandalwood is worth over a thousand dollars."

msgctxt "an5.44:7.7"
msgid "taṃ me bhagavā paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr "May the Buddha please accept it from me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:7.8"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā anukampaṃ upādāya."
msgstr "So the Buddha accepted it out of compassion."

msgctxt "an5.44:7.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uggaṃ gahapatiṃ vesālikaṃ iminā anumodanīyena anumodi:"
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha rejoiced with Ugga with these verses of appreciation:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:8.1"
msgid "“Manāpadāyī labhate manāpaṃ,"
msgstr "“The giver of the agreeable gets the agreeable,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ujjubhūtesu → ujubhūtesu (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.44:8.2"
msgid "Yo ujjubhūtesu dadāti chandasā;"
msgstr "enthusiastically giving clothing, bedding,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sayanamannapānaṃ → sayanamathannapānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.44:8.3"
msgid "Acchādanaṃ sayanamannapānaṃ,"
msgstr "food and drink, and various requisites"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:8.4"
msgid "Nānāppakārāni ca paccayāni."
msgstr "to those of upright conduct."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: anuggahītaṃ → anaggahītaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.44:9.1"
msgid "Cattañca muttañca anuggahītaṃ,"
msgstr "Knowing the perfected ones to be like a field"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:9.2"
msgid "Khettūpame arahante viditvā;"
msgstr "for what’s given, offered and not held back,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:9.3"
msgid "So duccajaṃ sappuriso cajitvā,"
msgstr "a good person gives what’s hard to give:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:9.4"
msgid "Manāpadāyī labhate manāpan”ti."
msgstr "the giver of the agreeable gets the agreeable.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:10.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā uggaṃ gahapatiṃ vesālikaṃ iminā anumodanīyena anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha, having rejoiced with Ugga with these verses of "
"appreciation, got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.51"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho uggo gahapati vesāliko aparena samayena kālamakāsi."
msgstr "Then after some time Ugga passed away,"

#. VAR: Kālaṅkato → kālakato (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.44:11.2"
msgid "Kālaṅkato ca uggo gahapati vesāliko aññataraṃ manomayaṃ kāyaṃ upapajji."
msgstr "and was reborn in a group of mind-made gods."

msgctxt "an5.44:11.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane "
"anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At that time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an5.44:11.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho uggo devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ "
"jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho uggaṃ devaputtaṃ bhagavā "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, the glorious god Ugga, lighting up the entire Jeta’s "
"Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. The Buddha said "
"to him:"

msgctxt "an5.44:11.5"
msgid "“kacci te, ugga, yathādhippāyo”ti?"
msgstr "“Ugga, I trust it is all you wished?”"

msgctxt "an5.44:11.6"
msgid "“Taggha me, bhagavā, yathādhippāyo”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, it is indeed just as I wished.”"

msgctxt "an5.44:11.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uggaṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Ugga in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:12.1"
msgid "“Manāpadāyī labhate manāpaṃ,"
msgstr "“The giver of the agreeable gets the agreeable,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:12.2"
msgid "Aggassa dātā labhate punaggaṃ;"
msgstr "the giver of the foremost gets the foremost,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:12.3"
msgid "Varassa dātā varalābhi hoti,"
msgstr "the giver of the excellent gets the excellent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:12.4"
msgid "Seṭṭhaṃ dado seṭṭhamupeti ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr "the giver of the best gets the best."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an5.44:13.1"
msgid "Yo aggadāyī varadāyī,"
msgstr "A person who gives the foremost,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:13.2"
msgid "seṭṭhadāyī ca yo naro;"
msgstr "the excellent, the best:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:13.3"
msgid "Dīghāyu yasavā hoti,"
msgstr "they’re long-lived and famous"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.44:13.4"
msgid "yattha yatthūpapajjatī”ti."
msgstr "wherever they’re reborn.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.44:13.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
